the glacier M. Mametova at the foot of the peaks of Amangeldy and Pioner.\nIt offers a panorama of the Central part of the Tuyuksu glacier and the Kumbel spur in the West, where the tops of Lokomotiv, Kosmodemyanskaya, Molodezhnaya, and Titova are located. There are three passes in the Kumbel spur: Lokomotiv and Molodezhny, leading to The kumbelsu gorge, and Titova pass, leading to the Gorelnik gorge.\nFrom the Alpingrad Parking lot, through the Pioner and Uchitel passes, you can get to the Bogdanovich glacier, which gives rise to the Sauruksai river, which flows into the Left Talgar river. [[Manshuk Mametova]] pass leads to The left Talgar gorge on the \"Sunny glade\".{{citation needed|date=March 2020}} From the Parking lot \"Alpingrad\" ascents are made to the peaks of Amangeldy, the pioneer-Teacher array, Panfilov Heroes, Manshuk Mametova, Antikainen. Then there is the well-known moraine lake No. 6.\nThe Mynzhylki mountain plateau is located at the source of the Little (Malaya) Almaatinka river, 28 kilometers South of [[Almaty]].{{citation needed|date=March 2020}} The tract is surrounded by Tuyuksu glaciers. To get to mynzhilki, first you need to get to Medeo, then it is convenient to continue on the cable car to cimbulak, and then on foot-5.7&nbsp;km. the Road goes all the way to the plateau, the climb is not steep, starting from the \"Tuyuksu Gate\", it becomes harder to go \u2014 the height and slope increases. The weather, as elsewhere in the mountains, can change suddenly, especially outside the \"Gate\", where tourists are often met by a strong headwind. Above the beginning of the trail to \"Alpingrad\", between the right slope and the moraines of the Tuyuksu glacier, there are two more Parking lots - \"Tashkent\" and\"Black stone\". Parking \"Tashkent\" is a small enclosed grassy area, not blown by the winds. That's why it's warm in the Parking lot. The \"Black stone\" Parking lot is located above and is named after a characteristic large stone of dark color. From these sites, ascents are made to the tops of the Tuyuksu glacier circus, located in the Malo-Almaty spur, or category passes are passed in the Malo-Almaty spur, South of Mametova peak, leading to the Left Talgar gorge.\n\n==Protection and visit==\nThe Ile-Alatau state national natural Park<ref>http://www.ile-alatau.kz</ref> Administration is responsible for the preservation and protection of the monument. It has a favorable acoustic environment (silence, melodic sounds in nature). Recommended visiting periods: may - October. The route is avalanche-prone, namely after snowfall and in the spring.\n\n== Sources ==\n* [https://monographies.ru/en/book/section?id=13066 Ivashchenko A. A. Reserves and national parks of Kazakhstan. \u2014 Almaty: \"Almatykitap\", 2006. - Pp. 216-223. - 281 p.]\n* [http://www.ile-alatau.kz Ile-Alatau state national natural Park. - Almaty, 2015. - Pp. 25-26. - 208 p.]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Kazakhstan]]\n[[Category:Almaty Region]]\n", "name_user": "Darwinek", "label": "safe", "comment": "+Category:Plateaus of Asia; \u00b1Category:Kazakhstan\u2192Category:Landforms of KazakhstanusingHotCat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mynzhylky_mountain_plateau"}
